quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,76,"And We had gripped them with suffering [as a warning], but they did not yield to their Lord, nor did they humbly supplicate, [and will continue thus]"
  23,77,"Until when We have opened before them a door of severe punishment, immediately they will be therein in despair."
  23,78,"And it is He who produced for you hearing and vision and hearts [i.e., intellect]; little are you grateful."
  24,58,"O you who have believed, let those whom your right hands possess and those who have not [yet] reached puberty among you ask permission of you [before entering] at three times: before the dawn prayer and when you put aside your clothing [for rest] at noon and after the night prayer. [These are] three times of privacy{1} for you. There is no blame upon you nor upon them beyond these [periods], for they continually circulate among you - some of you, among others. Thus does Allāh make clear to you the verses [i.e., His ordinances]; and Allāh is Knowing and Wise.",footnotes:1:[Literally, "exposure" or "being uncovered."]
  24,59,"And when the children among you reach puberty, let them ask permission [at all times] as those before them have done. Thus does Allāh make clear to you His verses; and Allāh is Knowing and Wise."
  24,60,"And women of post-menstrual age who have no desire for marriage - there is no blame upon them for putting aside their outer garments [but] not displaying adornment. But to modestly refrain [from that] is better for them. And Allāh is Hearing and Knowing."
  25,22,"The day they see the angels{1} - no good tidings will there be that day for the criminals, and [the angels] will say, ",footnotes:1:[i.e., at the time of death.],footnotes:2:[Referring to any good tidings.]
  25,23,"And We will approach [i.e., regard]{1} what they have done of deeds and make them as dust dispersed.",footnotes:1:[On the Day of Judgement.]
  25,24,"The companions of Paradise, that Day, are [in] a better settlement and better resting place."
